      <scopecontent>
         <head>Scope and Content Information</head>
         <p>Albemarle County, Virginia, miscellaneous records,
         1808-1861, consisting of: a) unidentified plat, 1 March 1808,
         of 117 acres in Albemarle County made by William Tompkins; b)
         unidentified plat, 17 April 1837, of 738 1/2 acres made by D.
         H. Goodman; c) promissory note, 18 September 1858, from O. W.
         Purvis and J. W. Mason to Peter F. Jefferson, for a note of
         $60 as second installment for puchase of two tenements in
         Scottsville, Virginia; d) agreement, 2 February 1861, between
         Samuel W. Goodman and O. W. Purvis, for money due Purvis for
         the purchase of a slave; and e) unidentified and undated
         plat.</p>
      </scopecontent>
